headline: Array completes sale of select spectrum assets to AT&T for $1.018 billion
summary: Array Digital Infrastructure, Inc.SM (NYSE: AD) (ArraySM) today announced the successful closing of the previously announced agreement with AT&T (NYSE: T) to sell a portion of the Company's retained spectrum licenses for total consideration of $1.018 billion.

headline: T Expands IoT Connectivity Portfolio: Will it Boost Prospects?

headline: Is AT&T (T) Pricing Reflect Its DCF Value After Recent Share Price Weakness
summary: If you are wondering whether AT&T’s current share price reflects its true worth, you are not alone. This article will walk through what the numbers are saying about the stock’s value. AT&T recently closed at US$23.74, with returns of a 3.9% decline over 7 days, a 3.4% decline over 30 days, a 3.3% decline year to date, 14.9% over 1 year, 43.4% over 3 years, and 45.4% over 5 years.
